title: Barangay 143
synopsis: Two years before the start of the series, Roberto "Coach B" Sebastián, Sr.'s son, Roberto "Basti" Sebastián, Jr., was killed by a gunman from a large syndicate which brought down the Barangay 143's Powerhouse team and led to today's events. Bren Park, a player for a Korean basketball team, had lost recently his family in a tragic accident during a snowstorm in South Korea that led him to quit basketball. However, following a revelation that he was his mother's child to a Filipino man, Bren went to Manila to search for him. Along the way, he joined a local basketball team, the Puzakals of Barangay 143.
background:
Its production started in Quezon City-based ASI Studios, a joint venture between Filipino firm Synergy88 and Singaporean company August Media Holdings is the production company behind Barangay 143.

TV Asahi is responsible for Barangay 143's direction as well as coming up with character designs for the series. ASI Studios wrote the script and lead the production of the series.

A Comeback GMA Network Sylvia Sanchez to voice Kapitana Baby Dela Cruz but replaced by actress Lorna Tolentino.

It is described by the producers as a "360-degree concept" and a story of love, hubris, drama, crime, and basketball.

The anime series is initially produced in Tagalog by a "celebrity cast"

In July 2018, the voice cast was announced, along with a new release date and a television network to air too.

Barangay 143 is primarily targeted towards the youth/young-adult market of the Philippines and is planned to be released in other Southeast Asian countries as well. Aside from Tagalog, Barangay 143 will also have an English-language release. It was first reported to air in the Philippines in Spring 2017. In July 2018, the series is announced to air on GMA Network in October 2018.

It is yet to be announced if the series is to be broadcast in Japan.

TV Asahi and August Rights, August Media Holdings' distribution arm will be responsible for the international distribution of the anime.

The series went on hiatus in December 2018, and while it was expected to return in February, it was announced it will return in early April 2019.

The series also premiered on Netflix on October 1, 2020, where it became one of the "most-watched titles" in Netflix Asia. The series was released on the Filipino streaming service POPTV on November 18.

A second season was announced on November 28. It was released on December 12 on POPTV.

At that time, Xiaohaiwa, who lost her home due to the Japanese raids, was rescued by her second brother, the Sheep Baby. In the process of following Erxiao to deliver the chicken feather letter, he gradually learned to be calm and brave, and to protect the chicken feather letter that was about to be exposed again and again. After the second elementary school was brutally killed by the devils in order to cover Haiwa and Ji Maoxin, Haiwa was no longer a coward who would pee her pants when she saw a devils in the first place. He took on the unfinished letter delivery task of the second elementary school, used his wit and perseverance to escape the devil’s blockade, and delivered the chicken feather letter to the Eighth Route Army intact, so that the Eighth Route Army could arrange for the transfer of the villagers and the wounded as soon as possible. The battle was deployed and the battle was won. Xiao Haiwa grew from a coward to a brave messenger hero, which deeply shocked Chen Yuxuan's heart. In Songshan Juci Mountain and Jishuihe area, there lived a primitive tribe called the Xiong clan, which lived on gathering, fishing, and hunting to the agricultural civilization. Its leader is Shaodian. The son of Shaodian was named Xuanyuan because he was born in Xuanyuan Hill.　　　 In addition to the Xiong Country, there are also small tribes in the Central Plains, such as the Gu family, the Pai family, the Yao family, the Kuo family, and the Hu family.　　　 Xuanyuan is exceptionally talented, he was born magical, clever in his childhood, agile and wit, he is virtuous in adulthood, resolute and courageous, and ambitious. In addition to studying every day, she also washes clothes for others to make money to support her father. By chance, Princess Tutu and Jiatu switched identities. The little prince of the Poisonous Mushroom Kingdom is sick and needs the "heart" of Princess Tutu to be cured. Duogu and Shitai want to use "Princess Tutu's mind" to fulfill their dreams of a rich man. The desert fox wants to use "Princess Bunny's Mind" in exchange for a lot of bounty. As a result, many interesting stories have occurred, and Princess Tutu is also constantly growing and learning to change. In the end, the little prince’s illness was cured by the doctor Tutu invited to. Princess Tutu and Jiatu also exchanged identities and returned to their original lives, and they became very good friends. (translated from iqiyi)

The five-color mushrooms are spiritual things, which can turn into star-like dots and get into your mouth, and you can taste what you want. The goat teacher told Jiatu that his ancestors once wrote a mythical story, describing the ancestors who went through hardships and came to the place where the five-color mushrooms lived. It was a paradise-like world where animals and animals are in harmony with each other. Living happily in that world is the paradise of animals... For the throne chair, Stacy and Duogu set out to find the magic mushroom. Rabbits, goats, and little princes also went to find magic mushrooms. After many obstacles, everyone finally arrived at the animal paradise. They boarded a boat and went down a stream, with a peach grove on one side, and the peach blossoms were red. The stream is full of boats, along a long bluestone road, through the cave, the cave is suddenly open, surrounded by mountains, flat in the middle, and magic mushrooms grow on the island in the pool below a waterfall. A monkey suddenly jumped out of the hole in the middle of the waterfall, saying, "I have been waiting for you for more than a thousand years, and you are finally here." (translated from iqiyi)

Before leaving, a magical stone flew close to Qiqi's pocket. At night, the stone suddenly glowed, and a spirit appeared. The elves claim to be noisy, come from Dream Manor, and can summon him through this gem. Qiqi and Lele are longing for Dream Manor, so the elves take them to the beautiful Dream Manor. Their arrival made the originally quiet manor become lively. During the period, they and the small animals in the manor experienced many stories. Under the care of everyone, Dream Manor has become even more beautiful... (translated from iqiyi)

title: Meng Meng Da Lianmeng
synopsis: The story of "Mengmenda Alliance" takes place on the ancient and mysterious Dunyuk continent, which is neatly divided into three areas. To the north are the tall and barren Gobi Mountains and sandy deserts, and the middle is full of dense trees. The forests and the grasslands with an infinite view, the south is the hills of strange peaks and strange ridges. For hundreds of years, the United Kingdom of the Desert Dead in the North and the United Kingdom of the Desa City-State in the South have been in confrontation and warfare for a long time, and countless heroes have risen and died in the flames of war. In order to maintain the balance of power and peace on the Dunyuk continent, the primitive races who guarded the forest and the peace-loving heroes established the Union of Guardians. They separated the Civil War by guarding the forest. At the same time, it also makes the forest for balance full of complex and difficult battles. There are mainly eight races living in Dunyuk: the Stanks who are good at magic, the blue blood who are good at gunpowder, the alien bears who are good at speed, the powerful desert dead in the north, and the Desa people who established the Desa dynasty in the south. Medieval Han people in the mountains and forests, as well as the Qiman and Giants (translated from tenceng)

title: High-Rise Invasion
synopsis: On the roof of a high-rise building, a young girl named Yuri witnesses a masked figure split a man’s head open with an axe! It’s not exactly an everyday occurrence for a high schooler, but things only get weirder from there. Yuri soon finds herself in a strange world of skyscrapers with only two options for escape—fight past the mysterious masked figures or leap to her death!
background: High-Rise Invasion (Japanese: 天空侵犯, Hepburn: Tenkū Shinpan) is a Japanese manga series written by Tsuina Miura and illustrated by Takahiro Oba. The series was serialized online in DeNA's Manga Box app from December 2013 to March 2019, with Kodansha compiling it into 21 tankōbon volumes. The manga is licensed in North America by Seven Seas Entertainment. A sequel manga titled High-Rise Invasion Arrive (天空侵犯arrive, Tenkū Shipan Arrive) began serialization in Kodansha's Magazine Pocket website and app in July 2019, with 4 tankōbon volumes released so far. An original net animation (ONA) anime series adaptation by Zero-G will stream worldwide on Netflix in February 2021.
